outline:
1. to pull out, pull up, set out, journey, remove, set forward, depart
    1. (Qal)
      1. to pull out or up
      2. to set out, depart
      3. to journey, march
      4. to set forth (of wind)
    2. (Niphal) to be pulled up, be removed, be plucked up
    3. (Hiphil)
      1. to cause to set out, lead out, cause to spring up
      2. to remove, quarry
kjv_def: cause to blow, bring, get, (make to) go (away, forth, forward, onward, out), (take) journey, march, remove, set aside (forward), [idiom] still, be on his (go their) way.
strongs_def: properly, to pull up, especially the tent-pins, i.e. start on ajourney
